From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0003/N] JvmMapfile.gmk: accept bsd target alongside linux

CheriBSD (OPENJDK_TARGET_OS=bsd) uses the same nm/awk symbol-export
discipline as Linux: GNU binutils nm, ELF .symtab. The macosx, aix,
and windows branches differ; bsd doesn't need its own branch — it
can share Linux's.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §5

--- a/make/hotspot/lib/JvmMapfile.gmk
+++ b/make/hotspot/lib/JvmMapfile.gmk
@@ -52,7 +52,7 @@ endif
 # Create a dynamic list of symbols from the built object files. This is highly
 # platform dependent.

-ifeq ($(call isTargetOs, linux), true)
+ifeq ($(call isTargetOs, linux bsd), true)
   DUMP_SYMBOLS_CMD := $(NM) --defined-only *.o
   ifneq ($(FILTER_SYMBOLS_PATTERN), )
     FILTER_SYMBOLS_PATTERN := $(FILTER_SYMBOLS_PATTERN)|
